{"ts":"2026-07-12T12:25:25.346Z","author":"maintainer-agent","op":"create","patch":[{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/id","value":"pm-qfdd"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/title","value":"cli/main.ts commander program is a module-level singleton: dynamically registered extension commands/flags persist across in-process invocations"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/description","value":"Third member of the pm-8fxc re-entrancy class, found while validating the pm-kvd0 worker bridge: 'const program = new Command()' lives at module scope (src/cli/main.ts:2494), and registerDynamicExtensionCommandPaths/addRuntimeFieldOption mutate that singleton per invocation. One-shot processes discard the mutations by exiting, but any long-lived host observes cross-invocation leakage: a kit extension registering --kit-note on core 'list' in workspace A makes 'pm list --type Task' in unrelated workspace B fail usage-validation ('Unknown option --type for extension command list. Expected one of: --kit-note'), and a 'pm --no-extensions beads import' after an earlier beads install in another workspace returns generic-failure instead of unknown_command. The pm-8fxc entry resets (snapshot caches + active-extension registries) cannot cover commander's own command/option registry. Interim isolation: the test bridge disposes its worker per test context. Real fix: construct the program per invocation inside runPmCli (or an unregister seam for dynamic paths) — a prerequisite for true SDK embedding of the CLI runtime; sequence with the pm-yh8r decomposition seam and pm-usfg SDK-first slices."},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/type","value":"Issue"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/status","value":"open"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/priority","value":2},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/tags","value":["area:cli","defect-class","re-entrancy","sdk-first"]},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/created_at","value":"2026-07-12T12:25:25.346Z"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/updated_at","value":"2026-07-12T12:25:25.346Z"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/author","value":"maintainer-agent"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/estimated_minutes","value":240},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/acceptance_criteria","value":"runPmCli invocations are fully re-entrant in one process: dynamic extension commands/flags registered by invocation N are invisible to invocation N+1 unless re-discovered from the active workspace; existing one-shot CLI behavior and startup latency unchanged; test bridge no longer needs per-test worker disposal"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/risk","value":"medium"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/confidence","value":"medium"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/dependencies","value":[{"id":"pm-8fxc","kind":"related","created_at":"2026-07-12T12:25:25.346Z"},{"id":"pm-yh8r","kind":"related","created_at":"2026-07-12T12:25:25.346Z"}]}],"before_hash":"3cc22dff72be7b14824654a7a64ea62b04799939b2fee54c1b5f52ca60bf6df0","after_hash":"ba9069c3f90b71c0926e20e7f8383b89228c1cf75d193f3a850cef073b60aeba","message":""}
